parameters:
\CLAfter that, I was taken in by the village chief,
but having lost everything, I just spent my days
doing nothing.

\CLHe was undoubtedly the one who created the
opportunity to change someone like me.
Hello! I'm Aeru, what's your name?
You have a strange way of speaking, don't you?

I don't have any memories from before coming here,
so even the name I was given by the village chief
might not be my real name.

I have nothing, so surely it's meaningless to be
with me.

Yeah, I was able to understand the letters you
showed me the other day.

Is that so! Then, I'll lend you an interesting
book for you to read!

By the way, have you ever seen a flower field?
There's a place where lots of beautiful white
flowers bloom!
What a waste... Alright! Let's go see it now!

On the way, there's a beautiful hill, right?
There's also a river where you can catch big
fish... and also...

\CLIn the end, we were dragged around until the sun
set, and when we returned, the village chief
scolded us a lot.

\CLEach experience with Aeru was wonderful, and with
each memory we made, my heart became richer.

\CLSince losing my memory, I have been made up of
memories with Aeru.

\CLIt may be a little different from the old me, but
the days I spent with Aeru and everyone were
definitely happy.

\CLWhile I was saved, there is still a girl crying
alone.

\CLI want to save her. I want her to bask in the
sunlight and laugh together, instead of shutting
herself away in a dark place.

Enter from the door next to the tool shop. I
didn't come here to play today.
I came to buy some items, you know!
Enter through the door right next to us.
